\ncan only be simultaneously reproduced when we include a tapered edge\nprescription for the surface density profile. The best model suggests that most\nof the disk mass is placed within a radius of $R<$ 50AU. Finally, we derive a\ndynamical mass for the central object of $M_{*}$=1.5$\\pm$0.2M$_{\\odot}$,\ncomparable to the one estimated with evolutionary models for an age of\n$\\sim$10Myr.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Jan 2015 17:04:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-18"}
